<p><br><br><strong>Proposed solution</strong></p>
<p><s>We add a column to AssetTypeProperty called OwnerCompanyId. This comp=
any has created the property and is thus the only company that can edit the=
 value of the property. Whether the property itself (type and name) can sti=
ll be edited/deleted is a different question.</s></p>
<p><s>Proposed business rules:</s></p>
<ul>
<li><s>Only the company that created a static property is allowed to change=
 the property's value</s></li>
<li><s>Only the company that created a static property is allowed to define=
 if a property can be seen by other companies (public)</s></li>
<li><s>Properties with origin sensor are always public</s></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-6.1.4SecurityArchive-6.Who/whatdecideswhichcompanycanmanage/vi=
ewwhichassets?">6. Who/what decides which company can manage/view which ass=
ets?</h3>
<p><br><strong>Proposed solution</strong><br>Leclanch=C3=A9 should assign t=
his administrative task to it's engineers whenever they setup a new asset (=
see SRS &gt; 7. Asset Management (TBD))</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-6.1.4SecurityArchive-7.WehavedefinedfunctionalityforFilters,wh=
ichinessencegenerateDataSets,shouldweaddrole-basedsecurityonthese?">7. We h=
ave defined functionality for Filters, which in essence generate DataSets, =
should we add role-based security on these?</h3>
<p>Conclusion: Proposed solution is the desired solution.<br><strong>Propos=
ed solution</strong></p>
<p>As defined in&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://leclanche.=
atlassian.net/wiki/display/RAS/1.3+Report+Filters" rel=3D"nofollow">1.3 Rep=
ort Filters</a>&nbsp;we can define a dataset that consists of a selected nu=
mber of assets with their selected set of properties.</p>
<p>If we specify for each of these filters, using roles, whom has access to=
 them, we can already control the viewing access of our data. And not only =
for static data but for all data.</p>
<p>This is also contained on a company level as each company would have the=
ir own filters. This would imply that by default each company would have ac=
cess to all the sensor properties.</p>
<p>Proposed business rules:</p>
<ul>
<li>Every filter is stored on a company level</li>
<li>A filter can not be shared among different companies</li>
<li>A filter can be secured for editing by specifying which roles should be=
 allowed</li>
<li>A filter can be secured for viewing by specifying which roles should be=
 allowed</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-6.1.4SecurityArchive-8.Who/whatdefineswhocanedit/viewcertainpr=
operties?">8. Who/what defines who can edit/view certain properties?</h3>
<p>Not necessary, every company has the same access to the asset<br><strong=
>Proposed solution</strong></p>
<p><s>It has to be defined in the UI but it should not become an annoying a=
dministrative task.</s></p>
<p><s>We want to use roles to define access on the property level</s></p>
<p><s>We want to use roles to define access to assets</s></p>
<p><s>Proposal for property level security: An administrator defines securi=
ty levels per assettype</s></p>
